6:
Whoa, wait up! I'm an organic! I
can't move like that!
19:
Nate, behind you! They're gonna get
away!
31:
Hm... Well, leaving Alk in the dust
was bound to happen, but...
34:
Then there's the property damage
and the fact that you almost let a
suspect escape.
47:
Hold on... I also didn't see the
suspect until it was almost too late...
51:
Fine, then both of you are at fault.
Happy? You know, I wasn't expecting
the number of issues to INCREASE
when we signed you on.
54:
Not that we weren't anticipating a
few hiccups along the way. But just
as a reminder...
58:
At Paradigm Break Company, we
grab hold of the future we want and
never let go. We expect you to do
the same when representing us.
Understood?
61:
Now get back to work! I expect a
letter of apology regarding this
incident later!
69:
Do you want sugar or milk with your
coffee?
84:
I know I keep getting in my own way.
I should be able to do these jobs no
problem, but I keep screwing up.
88:
But can't they lower their
expectations a bit?! Sure, they SAY
following the AI should be enough,
but obviously it's NOT!
95:
It's my fault the boss yelled at you
like that...
108:
Yup! I even roasted the beans
myself!
111:
Like Johnson said, they anticipated
a few bumps in the road. It's fine.
114:
Still... Racing off on my own like that
was real dumb.
117:
Eh, you were trying to get to the
scene of the crime as fast as you
could. That's a good thing in my
books.
122:
You know... I thought you were
another idiot duped by Johnson, but
you're actually a pretty nice guy.
126: Your opinion of me was that low?!
130:
I think I just... have a hard time
focusing.
133:
First, there's the stuff happening in
front of me, and then on top of that,
I've got stuff going on in my head
too. It's a lot.
136:
You see, I've got a combat AI
installed in me.
139:
It can control everything from my
movements to my emotions during
combat. It can even analyze my
current situation and come up with
an effective strategy.
145:
Isn't it? But the fact that I can't get
the hang of it means I'm the worst of
the worst.
148: I know I need to do better, but...
152: You can't do it all, right?
155:
In that case, why don't you leave the
backup to me and turn off those
extra functions?
159:
In return, I'll leave the rushing in to
you. You're good at that part, right?
162:
We'll make Johnson do a double
take so hard, he hurts his neck.
166: You really think I can manage that?
170: ...Well, we won't know until we try.
174:
Come on, you could at least lie a
little and say, "Yeah, for sure!" or
something...
177:
I just don't know if Johnson's the
type to admit he was wrong about
you.
182: ...Yeah, I won't get my hopes up.
186:
Au contraire! Facing your failures is
the key to future growth and
success!
191:
Now that you've had your little team
huddle, it's time we got back to
discussing the future!
196:
D-don't scare me like that! How long
have you been here?!
200:
Ah, youth truly is a beautiful thing.
The two of you almost made this old
man cry.
204:
But never mind that! Alk, I've got
something for you, so follow me!
208:
Introducing the latest craze to
sweep the streets of Qualia City...
PBC Hero Gadget No. 169—the
self-driving robocycle! No license
required!
212:
Hold on, this is for me?! Whoa... This
is so cool!
216:
Wait... Isn't this the bike from Metal
Maniac Paradigm? Is this, uh... legal?
What about copyright infringement?
224:
Ah, you know, that classic superhero
comic with—
229:
Well, I'm glad to see you two getting
along! But enough chitchat. Get out
there and take this baby for a test
spin!
232:
Don't get any funny ideas though.
This is just a patrol. You two can go
on your date later.
238:
Wh-who said anything about a
date?!
